caption: I noticed it while walking. It’s beautiful, so I stopped by took a photo and share it with other people. I couldn’t find more info about it, it would be nice if people from Nancy would write more details in the description about its history, anecdotes etc. I am sure there is a lot to tell!

A chance discovery. Walked past this equestrian statue of Joan of Arc in an almost obscure street in Nancy. I don't know much about it and not mentioned in "things to discover in Nancy" but happy to have past and seen it. I read up it's history after and it was erected in 1890 in a square bearing her name. Not much else except it's a magnificent monument to see. It's not every tourist's cup of tea, but if you stumble across it, pause and explore.
not very nice from you to burn me down and then build a statue in my honour >:(
a beautiful statue of the symbol of Lorraine
I loved standing under the statue, in the direction the horse was looking (as in the photo, normally, attached); guaranteed effect for a mind that has not forgotten its creativity! :P
When I was a kid and I saw this statue, I knew we had arrived in Nancy
